[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering Testcontainers Setup**\n\nI’m thinking about the necessary entries to set up Testcontainers before generation. Should I include the dependency \"org.testcontainers:testcontainers:<version>\"? If I go with a stable version, 1.19.8 looks good since it has metadata. Alternatively, I could choose the latest version.\n\nThe repository already has the necessary metadata for 1.19.8, which makes it seem like a good choice. However, if tests compile and run on JVM and native images, I wonder if that metadata is sufficient for reachability when running tests. Should I consider using a Pulsar Mock instead?\n\n**Examining Pulsar Client API Stats**\n\nI want to look into the statistics for the pulsar-client-api. There are probably many dynamic calls in the pulsar-client, but a lot can be covered offline, such as parsing POJOs for AVRO/JSON, the authentication plugin, and cryptography aspects. The documentation mentions \"normal use\" starts with the standalone setup. Should I fetch the source documentation? I wonder if using Javadoc is the best approach. Let’s check out the Pulsar docs to get more details.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_05a1b3a78bafa6be016a28fa0738888190983d16289935ca38\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqKPoaeDQoFUUo9ijNrj-bYiJUQlYh8XMqTQ0VLctt4ewWmo0ryJ9mxDe-5lrhVHMOxrOYINeGc113wKrXch3TqR674hc_fZYPeOdL9eqFmws21yLz1of9ROz3paAZwx5tmWCO5hqLM1lVq-dKlUBViG5F15inY5r36fmhqmr6QLj8gKf0_FkPXTwv4oX0UWh0sAFaf1M4B7PN23Y5YTWiik9Yg5zZSIKyXUzJFvmcM3Yppr3jt1TTu0W3IqWCmfi7-yxXbjJYPQVooU2cv0-X5JgbckW4MjawcS6l57JPOM_h29RWdNLGZFXwObjH5DDhwqVBGJgTTXOnWY2hDz-cWEwhe3ScbhvUTNtQZ51Kl3NLE6j60apg_xcdX-5KRqsPsOLFCsdiuYuGABhTfSiY2VPemO2UCs4L4csqHELG5edZDhTtfvtiwCIZbJYlAc_AnAyDWHLbA3gJ3H61huk4vYJSFaG5anYgz6I9_v4l1JqrkJBICdYbg9ao7bx3xwEjNFXmoMHz88_yXB7W5L9b8YYb7HW1IO_-WeE5W-HcQlELRG0bR6bBvLv292SRAhxJ9GPuz3TJ1e3K4ZOHwXLmWo7ODlYwUJnt